modules.description: This module provides operations to configure logging parameters like verbosity levels, timestamp formatting, and output destinations, while supporting colored log output and counters. It works with enumerated types for log levels (e.g., debug, info) and colors, timezone identifiers, and integer/string conversions for level representation. Typical use cases include dynamically adjusting log verbosity, customizing log aesthetics for terminal readability, and redirecting logs to files or streams.
